Elektrenai Vocational Training Centre focuses on education of practical skills not in school, but in real work situations. In this case graduated students could start work without additional training at workplaces. Companies at Elektrenai municipality can’t provide enough place for professional practice, therefore international internships by this project would be very advantageous for both students and EPMC.

Project’s participants:  vocational training second-third course students of automobiles electro-technician, forwarding agent of logistics, builder-constructions finisher, cook-waiter, computer equipment adjuster and mechatronic professions (total 39 students and 6 accompanying teachers).

Internship countries: United Kingdom, Germany, Malta, Italy, Czech Republic, Spain.

Project’s main goal – to improve professional skills and competences of vocational training students at workplaces, to educate their practical skills at real work situations:
• automobiles electro-technicians: to be able to make technical service of right-hand wheel steering cars’ control and steering devices and parts.
• forwarding agents of logistics: to be able to prepare and accomplish orders of online sales; to get familiar with logistics of online sales.
• builder-constructions finishers: to be able to do façade restauration works, to get familiar with methods of restauration.
• cooks-waiters: to be able to prepare traditional Italian dishes and to serve them.
• computer equipment adjusters: to be able to fix and maintain smart devices; to get familiar with structure of smart devices.
• Mechatronics: to be able to adjust and maintain automatic mechatronic systems of manufacturing.

Other objectives:
• To raise the level of students’ professional skills and competences at real work situations, especially taking into consideration their contribution to labor market of today;
• To educate foreign language and communicational skills in foreign environment, team work abilities;
• To raise the level of participants’ understanding of other cultures and tolerance towards surrounding people;
• To raise the level of self-confidence, to increase self-sufficiency and initiative skills.

Project’s activities:
• Preparation and sign of grant agreement;
• Information and selection of participants;
• Preparation of participants;
• Preparation of final programs of the internships;
• Agreements with participants and hosting partners;
• Organization and implementation of the internships;
• Submission of participants’ reports;
• Presentations of internship, certification of its participants;
• Implementation of planned dissemination;
• Submission of intermediate report;
• Submission of final report.

Project’s impact for participating organizations (corresponding to strategic aims of EPMC and hosting partners):
• Increased the level of international collaboration between educational institutions;
• Improved the process of vocational training by organizing international internships in real work places;
• Increased the level of collaboration between education and business institutions;
• Organizations’ staff will improve organizational and international management skills, will acquire competences of international management.
• By dissemination activities society will be introduced to the project and advantages of the EU support. This would lead to increasing number of students at EPMC and internship participants at hosting partners.

Project will make a positive impact for all students of EPMC. Internships’ opportunities and positive feedback of participants and public presentations of the implemented internships will increase the studying motivation of younger students, will help to achieve better learning outcomes.

Long-lasting impact for participating organizations: applying for new mobility projects and developing international collaboration. Long lasting impact will be assured by project’s dissemination, which will let for employers and potential students to know about the project.

Expected quantitative project’s results:
• Completed professional training of participants under the internships’ programs;
• Acquired internship’s evaluation certificates by all participants – Europass, certificates of hosting organizations and EPMC;
• Made reports of internships by all participants;
• Organized presentations of the internships;

Expected other project’s results:
• Raised level of the participants’ professional competences according to their professional requirements;
• In the real workplaces improved practical skills of participants giving better integration possibilities into labor market;
• Improved language and communication skills of the participants;
• Raised level of participants’ self-confidence, initiative skills, entrepreneurship, sociability as well as tolerance and cultural awareness;

Evaluation documents:
• Europass mobility document
• Certificate of hosting organization
• Certificate of EPMC

PROJECT’S PARTICIPANTS – vocational training II-III course students of vehicles’ business employee (auto-mechanic) and small business services provider professions.

PROJECT’S DURATION
2017 06 01 – 2018 05 31. There will be four internships: to Germany, United Kingdom, Italy and Malta. Total number of participants – 32 (plus 4 accompanying people).

PARTNERS:
Consortium composition: Aukštadvaris Agricultural School (project‘s coordinator), Elektrėnai Vocational Training Centre, Šilutė Agricultural School.
Hosting partners: Wisamar Bildungsgesellschaft gemeinnuetzige GmbH (Germany), Idea-M (United Kingdom), AMFI Agenzia per la Mobilità e la Formazione Internazionale (Italy), IZI Ltd (Malta).

PROJECT’S MAIN GOAL: to improve entrepreneurship and competitiveness of small business services provider and vehicles’ maintenance business employee (auto-mechanic) professions students providing them with possibilities to do international practice in foreign companies and to acquire new professional skills and competences.

OTHER OBJECTIVES
1. to educate the following specific professional competences of participants;
• for vehicles’ maintenance business employee (auto-mechanic) profession students:
-to be able to maintain chassis and transmissions of German-made cars; to know about ways of gas emission reduction (in Germany)
-to be able to maintain chassis and steering systems of right-side steering model cars’; to be able to do vehicles’ electronics diagnostics (in United Kingdom);
• for small business services provider profession students:
-to be able to coordinate different activities in company, to know business organization peculiarities (in Italy)
-to be able to organize development of small business for tourists and recreation, communicate with clients (in Malta)
2. to educate entrepreneurship, innovation, initiative skills;
3. to acquire better occupation and employment opportunities, improve perspectives of future career;
4. to educate participants’ awareness and understanding of other cultures and tolerance, to raise the level of participants’ self-confidence, self-esteem and sociability;
5. to improve participants’ foreign language and communicative skills;

PROJECTS WORK ACTIVITIES
• Preparation and signing of grant agreement;
• Participants information activities and selection;
• Preparation of participants;
• Final adjustment of internships’ programs;
• Organisation of internships;
• Signing agreements with partners and participants;
• Implementation of internships;
• Participants reports and questionnaire filling;
• Presentations of internships, certification;
• Dissemination;
• Preparation of final report.

EXPECTED PROJECT’S RESULTS
• Completed professional training under the internship programs (4 internships, total 32 participants);
• Acquired internship’s evaluation certificates (total 32 participants) – Europasses, certificates of hosting organizations and project’s coordinator.
• Made reports of internships (by all 32 participants);
• Raised level of the participants’ professional competences according to their professional requirements;
• Improved participants’ vocational skills, giving better employability opportunities in labour market;
• Raised level of participants’ self-confidence, initiative skills, entrepreneurship, sociability as well as tolerance and cultural awareness;
• Improved language and communication skills of participants;

EVALUATION DOCUMENTS
As the evaluation of acquired and improved skills, every participant will acquire:
• Europass
• Certificate of hosting organizations
• Certificate of coordinating organization

IMPACT
Small business services provider and vehicles’ maintenance business employee (auto-mechanic) professions students will do their international practice in foreign companies, will improve their entrepreneurship and competitiveness, will acquire new professional skills and competences.
Participants will acquire specific professional competences. International internship will enhance participants’ European dimension and tolerance, participants will acquire entrepreneurship, innovative and initiative skills. Long-lasting impact for participants: successfully passed qualifying examination, improved employability opportunities.

DISSEMINATION
Project’s dissemination main goal: to introduce target groups with project’s implementation, its goals, activities and results, to spread positive EU support possibilities and encourage people‘s tolerance, cultural awareness and understanding.
Methods of project’s dissemination: articles in web-pages and regional newspapers, posts in FB, stands and booklets about project, presentations of the internships and consideration of project’s results.

PROJECT’S PARTICIPANTS – graduates of auto-technician, builder, cook-waiter, small business services provider, secretary and electro-technician professions.

PROJECT’S DURATION
2017 06 01 – 2018 05 31, total 12 months. There will be three internships: to United Kingdom, Malta and Italy. Total number of participants – 22 graduates.

PROJECTS’ PARTNERS:
Consortium composition: Kaišiadorys School of Business and Technology (coordinator), Aukštadvaris Agricultural School, Elektrėnai Vocational Training Centre.
Hosting partners: Idea-M (United Kingdom), IZI Ltd. (Malta), AMFI (Italy)

PROJECT’S MAIN GOAL
To provide graduates with the possibilities to acquire real work place experience and specific professional competences in order to increase their employment opportunities and competitiveness.

OTHER OBJECTIVES
• to educate the following specific professional competences of participants;
-for auto-technicians: to be able to maintain chassis and steering systems of right-side steering model cars’ (in United Kingdom)
-for builders: to be able to do buildings’ renovation works, to know the methods of restoration (in United Kingdom)
- for cooks-waiters: to be able to make dishes, containing seafood, serve them properly to customers (in Italy)
- for small business services providers: to be able to organize small business for tourists and recreation, communicate with clients (in Italy)
- for secretaries: to be able to serve customers in English properly and communicate with international clients, administer company’s social networks (in Malta);
- for electro-technicians: to be able to install electricity installation in areas of higher humidity, its protection against fluctuation of voltage (in Malta)
• Try to achieve better employment opportunities of participants, improve their career prospects;
• In real work places improve graduates’ skills and competences, especially taking into consideration their contribution to labor market of today;
• Try to achieve that real work experience and acquired competences will be acknowledged in whole EU;
• To raise the level of participants’ self-confidence and sociability, to educate participants’ awareness and understanding of other cultures, tolerance;
• To create the environment, where participants could acquire entrepreneurship and initiative skills, self-sufficiency, abilities to work in business and different situations;
• To improve participants’ foreign language and communicative skills in foreign environment, team-work abilities, broaden cultural outlook.

IMPACT
During the internships graduates will acquire real work place experience and specific professional competences, will raise their employment opportunities and competitiveness.

Participants will improve their foreign language skills, team work abilities, raise the level of self-confidence, feel themselves stronger psychologically before entering labor market.

Impact for participating organizations:
• Raised the level of international collaboration
• Improved teaching process because of possibilities to acquire experience in real work places during the internships
• Raised the level of collaboration between educational organizations and business
• Organizations’ staff will improve their management skills and competences

Long lasting impact for participants will be assured by Europass and other acknowledgement certificates, which will strengthen participants’ diplomas and give better employment opportunities.

EXPECTED PROJECT’S RESULTS
• Completed professional training under the internship programs (3 internships, total 22 participants);
• Acquired real work experience;
• Acquired internship’s evaluation certificates (total 22 participants) – Europasses, certificates of hosting organizations and project’s coordinator;
• Made reports of internships (by all 22 participants);
• Raised level of the participants’ professional competences according to their professional requirements;
• In real workplaces improved practical skills of participants giving better integration possibilities into labour markets;
• Improved language and communication skills of participants;
• Raised level of participants’ self-confidence, initiative skills, entrepreneurship, sociability as well as tolerance and cultural awareness;

EVALUATION DOCUMENTS
As the evaluation of acquired and improved skills, every participant will acquire:
• Europass
• Certificate of hosting organizations
• Certificate of coordinating organization

DISSEMINATION
Project’s dissemination main goal: to introduce target groups with project’s implementation, its goals, activities and results, to spread positive EU support possibilities and encourage people‘s tolerance, cultural awareness and understanding.
Methods of project’s dissemination: articles in web-pages and regional newspapers, posts in FB, stands and booklets about project, presentations of the internships and consideration of project’s results.

European policies allow people to move abroad more easily. This, and the fact that sometimes workers have greater possibilities of finding a job abroad, make that European Citizens today are more likely to leave their own country in order to study or work in other EU countries than before. People are often compelled to move in order to follow the changes in the labour market, as some fields of work may be better developed in another country or there may be a lack of workers in a specific sector. Therefore, workers specialized in those areas are more likely to be successful abroad.

Driven by this necessity a person undergoing education or training should be aware of the situation and the opportunities of the European labour market. Teachers need to be able to transmit this new European dimension. 



The project of the Consortium 'Your ticket for Europe' aims to facilitate mobility for learners, teachers and staff in VET in  order to give them an international experience of high quality.

We want to make sure that students involved in mobility  are provided with all the tools they need in order to explore their chances of finding a job abroad. Awareness of the situation in the EU Labour market is the first necessary step to raise students'  awareness of their professional chances around Europe partly due to the elimination of international boundaries.



Teachers and staff should also be involved in mobility in order to exchange experiences and good practices with other teachers and to improve their skills and curricula. Involvement in mobility ensures that teachers are the first multipliers and will disseminate the positive outcomes of their experience.



Our objectives are:

• For learners:

           -support the development of their professional skills;

           -improve their employability and their competitiveness in the EU labour market;

           -develop their personal, social and multicultural skills;

           -improve their language skills.

• For teachers and trainers:

           -support their professional development ;

           -encourage international exchange;

           -share good practices and new teaching methods;

           -foster cooperation among European schools;

           -make them the first multipliers of the benefit of a mobility experience.



Specific activities will be:

-organisation of meetings in order to encourage the exchange of good practices among teachers and trainers;

-improvement of the support system for students and teachers before and after their mobility;

-organisation of seminars in order to exchange information about the opportunities of EU labour market.



The employability of youngsters increases due to the mobility experience in which they have:

-gained knowledge about their specific sector and the new methods used for that sector;

-collected information on the job opportunities in the labour market of the hosting country but also of other countries;

-learned how to approach the EU labour market (what should they know when they want to find a job abroad, where to look for it, which level of language proficiency should they have, cultural awareness).

The characteristic goal of quality mobility is to inform and  guide teachers and learners.

Information must be clear, accessible and easy to find. This information is provided through formal channels (such as flyers, brochures, conferences...) but also by using multipliers. Teachers, trainers, students and young workers who have already participated in mobility projects inspire, motivate and encourage other people to become mobile.

Seminars are organised in order to bring multipliers and possible participants into contact with each other. Multipliers will give their testimonials and mobility experts will help the participants with the required paperwork.

We ensure the quality of the mobility by establishing continuous dialogue and clear arrangements between the sending and the hosting institutions and by using learning agreements for the recognition of knowledge, skills and competences acquired (ECVET). In one particular case we want to organise training for assessors in the work field in Ireland and Spain in cooperation with Calibris (Dutch knowledge centre) so that we can ensure that in the future exams will take place according to Dutch regulations.

Moreover, personal assistance will be given to mobility participants by providing convenient and affordable facilities. Learners will be offered guidance on how to make the best use of learning mobility. At the end of the experience they will have developed their knowledge, skills and competences of their field and they will have become particularly aware of the opportunities within the European labour market, which is the new labour market in which every EU citizen can explore the chances of personal and professional growth.
